Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher 
Hong Kong stocks rebounded on Friday to stop a two-day consecutive
decline, with the key Hang Seng Index rising 115.85 points, or 1.07
percent, to close at 10,919.53 points.
The blue chip index dropped 73.36 points, or 0.67 percent, to register
10,730.32 at the opening bell for Friday morning's trading.
The shares rose 0.28 points to close at 10,803.96 at midday on Friday.
And the day's trading registered a turnover of 7,545 million HK dollars
(967.3 million U.S. dollars).
The Hang Seng Index fell 547.13 points, or 4.82 percent, to close at
10,803.68 on Thursday.
